- id: 28
  task: Add event-listener architecture rules — Adapter as unified event API layer
  note: |
    Missing rules for how events connect to logic across input sources.
    The pattern (from MVVM): one central adapter layer collects all event sources in one file —
    buttons, keyboard shortcuts, and MCP calls all register on the same named events.
    The logic layer listens in one place (one listener per event) and executes the action — it does
    not know whether the trigger came from UI, keyboard, or MCP.

    Core principles to describe:
    - The adapter file is the only place events are defined and exposed (API layer)
    - One listener per event — never duplicated logic across input sources
    - Input sources (button, shortcut, MCP) bind to the event, not to each other
    - The logic layer is unaware of input source (decoupling)
    - Naming: events named by intention, not by input source
      (e.g. `on_save`, not `on_ctrl_s_pressed` or `on_save_button_clicked`)

    Candidate location: ipc/event-adapter.md or global/event-adapter.md
    (ipc/ because it is communication between layers, not a language-specific pattern)
  pass: |
    New rule file describes the adapter pattern with RULE: lines for:
    - One adapter file per module/feature collecting all input sources
    - Only one logic callback per named event
    - Input sources register on events, logic registers on events — the two do not know each other
    - Forbidden: direct call from button handler to logic function (bypass of adapter)
  status: pending

